<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>BBC women's sport July 2013</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:center; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by the BBC [WAS0003]</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Summary</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Thank you for the opportunity to contribute to the Culture, Media and Sport Committee inquiry into the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">barriers that remain to women’s participation in sport and how they can be overcome. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC wishes to offer its views on the role that the broadcast media – in particular the BBC - can play to promote women’s participation in sport. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We believe the BBC is making a significant contribution to the promotion of women’s sport and to encouraging greater participation in sport. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC wishes to make the following points:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Delivering broadcast moments that bring the nation together can be very effective for showcasing sports and sporting role models, both male and female.   </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We recognise the importance of cross-platform coverage of a wide range of sports, not just those that deliver the biggest audiences. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC has strengthened further its commitment to coverage of women’s sport in the last year – including the appointment of an editorial lead. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our connection with audiences is enhanced through a diverse mix of on-air and off-air production talent.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We have launched a pan-BBC campaign targeted directly at encouraging greater participation in sport, leveraging the cross-platform reach and impact of BBC output. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Bringing the nation together</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC’s coverage of sport consistently generates massive audience figures across TV, radio and online. These broadcast events can be very effective for showcasing sports and sporting role models. Examples include the Wimbledon Championships, Olympic Games and Commonwealth Games.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In 2012 the BBC accounted for 2% of TV sports </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">output</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> hours in the UK but over 50% of TV sports </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">viewing</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> hours. This reflects the quality of the BBC’s sports coverage and its free-to-air availability. We also run the most popular live news &amp; sports radio station (5 live) and the most popular sports website (www.bbc.co.uk/sport) in the UK. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC’s coverage of London 2012, for example, demonstrated the power of sport to inspire and the impact of showcasing successful British competitors. A few examples for our female athletes include:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">16 million people tuned in to watch Jessica-Ennis Hill claim the Heptathlon title on Super Saturday. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">11 million tuned in to watch Rebecca Adlington claim Bronze in the pool.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">More than 9 million watched Victoria Pendleton claim Gold in the track cycling. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">4 million people watched as Team GB beat Brazil in front of a record 70,000 spectators at Wembley.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">At the end of the year over 14 million people tuned in to watch Sports Personality of the Year to relive the highlights of 2012 – with five of our female Olympians/Paralympians featuring on the shortlist for the main award. </span></li></ul><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There is a widespread expectation among the UK public that the major sporting events will be available on television on a universal, free-to-air basis. Listed events legislation is essential for ensuring maximum exposure to some of the biggest sporting events that, in turn, can help encourage participation.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">A survey undertaken by the BBC after London 2012 found that almost one-quarter of respondents believed that the BBC’s coverage of the Games encouraged them to take part in sport. This followed on from research contained in the BBC’s submission to the Government’s Free-to-Air Events Consultation which noted</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">“There is evidence that free-to-air access to major events can generate wider benefits such as fostering greater interest in sport and influencing participation, which in turn can deliver positive outcomes, both for the individual concerned (e.g. fitness, well-being) and for society at large...”</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">A breadth of sports coverage</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC recognises that it has a public service role (enshrined in its Framework Agreement) to support a wide range of sports - not just those that deliver big audiences. Indeed, some of the events we cover will attract lower audiences than could have been achieved by other (non-sports) programming.    </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We have always been a strong supporter of women’s sport. Even outside of the Summer Olympic Games we typically cover in the region of 15-20 different sports with female competitors on our network TV channels and Red Button TV interactive service each year. This sits alongside extensive coverage of women’s sport on the BBC’s radio and online services. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">When all the hours are added up – including repeat showings on HD channels and the Red Button – we estimate that approaching 1,000 TV hours of women’s sport are normally made available every year by the BBC. And that doesn’t include the 2,500 hours of live coverage of the London Olympics that we delivered last year, much of which featured those extraordinary successes touched on above. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">An enhanced commitment to women’s sport since London 2012</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In partnership with sports bodies, the BBC has strengthened further its commitment to women’s sport in the last twelve months across all broadcast platforms. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For example, we enhanced our broadcast portfolio with the acquisition of the TV rights to the 2013 Women’s European Football Championship. The BBC broadcast a live match from every night of the tournament, including all of England’s matches, the Semi Final and the Final – an unprecedented commitment to the tournament from a free-to-air broadcaster in the UK. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We presented the latter stages of the tournament from Sweden and all the matches on BBC Three achieved above the timeslot average for both share and reach, and audience appreciation scores were high. That being said, we are conscious of the significant challenges of delivering step changes in the impact of these events: a typical England </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Group Stage match in the Women’s European Football Championship attracted a peak audience of around 1 million, compared to the men’s equivalent last year of 10-15 million.        </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We believe the reach of the tournament could have been greater had it received more widespread support and coverage across the media. This highlights a more general point that the effective promotion of women’s sport requires a coordinated, pan-industry approach. The BBC will play an important role but it cannot alone overcome the barriers that exist. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC is continuing to support the development of women’s football, with live TV coverage of England’s home matches in the World Cup qualifiers plus four FA Women's Super League programmes on BBC Two – a terrestrial TV first.  The BBC Sport website now features a weekly goals package throughout the Super League season, there are live commentaries on 5 live Sports Extra and round-ups of the games on </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Sportsday</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> on the BBC News Channel. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Other examples of how we are working in partnership with sports bodies to  enhance our coverage of women’s sport include:</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Earlier this year, BBC Sport showed England’s Six Nations match at Twickenham against France live on the Red Button, along with a weekly round-up of the tournament. More recently, we brought audiences live cross-platform coverage of the Women’s British Golf Open. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">5 live Sports Extra provided live commentary of England’s netball series against Australia in early 2013 – believed to be a first for UK radio. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Despite not having the TV rights, the BBC sent a team to India to cover the Cricket World Cup - 5 live Sports Extra provided commentary of every England match and the Final, plus there were regular TV reports into Network News bulletins from the tournament.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Since mid-September 2012, 5 live’s discussion programme </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Sports Team </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">has carried out in-depth interviews with many leading female sport stars such as Sarah Storey, Ebony Rainford-Brent and Kate Walsh. More than three times as many sportswomen have appeared on the show post-Olympics compared to pre-Olympics.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BBC Breakfast’s Sally Nugent ran a week-long report exploring the issues surrounding women's participation in sport. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BBC Sport commissioned an ‘Elite British Sportswomen’ survey to coincide with International Women’s Day 2013 - coverage of the results appeared extensively on TV, radio and digital platforms.</span></li></ul><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC’s investment in women’s sport is being prioritised around coverage of Olympic &amp; Commonwealth sports (outside of Games time) and supporting our other major events. For example, the BBC provided live coverage of the tennis from Eastbourne on TV and radio in the run-up to Wimbledon this year – opportunities to build the profile of emerging talent such as Laura Robson and Heather Watson.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Connecting with audiences</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We believe it is important to offer a diverse mix of on-air presenters, pundits and reporters to make our coverage more inclusive and better connect with audiences. It requires significant investment over a long period of time to build the journalistic skills and experience required to work on live sports programming. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC’s roster of female presenters, reporters and pundits is arguably the strongest of any media organisation in the UK. By way of example:   </span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Gabby Logan’s portfolio includes athletics, the Olympic magazine show ‘Inspire’ and rugby union.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Sue Barker’s portfolio includes coverage of tennis and skating. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Clare Balding’s portfolio includes coverage of the Olympic and Commonwealth Games. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Hazel Irvine’s portfolio includes golf and snooker, and she will be joining Clare at the Winter Olympics in Sochi.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Suzi Perry, Lee McKenzie &amp; Jennie Gow are all part of our cross-platform coverage of Formula 1, alongside Azi Farni on MotoGP.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In addition to their usual on-air roles, Jacqui Oatley (TV/radio), Sally Nugent (BBC Breakfast) &amp; Tina Da</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">heley (Radio 1) led TV coverage of the Women’s European Football Championship. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Rebecca Adlington recently joined the BBC TV team at the World Swimming Championships, while Paula Radcliffe and Denise Lewis are closely involved with our coverage of athletics throughout the summer. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our sports news presenters have a strong female contingent, including Karthi Gnanasegaram, Lizzie Greenwood-Hughes and Katherine Downes – with Natalie Pirks recently joining the team as Sports News Correspondent.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">              </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For the new football season, Amy Lawrence and Kelly Cates will be regulars on 5 live’s </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Monday Night Club</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">606</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Charlotte Green will be taking over from James Alexander Gordon this season as the new voice of the classified football results on BBC Radio. </span></li></ul><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It is not just on-air where BBC Sport has recognized the importance of building a diverse workforce and better representing the audiences we serve.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC appointed its first ever female Director of Sport (Barbara Slater) in 2009. 5 of the 11 Board members of BBC Sport are now female with many more women in senior editorial positions across the department. This is a key part of our succession planning, sitting alongside other targeted initiatives. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">BBC Sport has appointed an editorial lead for women’s sport (Shelley Alexander), working across broadcast platforms in order to explore ways of enhancing our coverage. A key aspect of the role is working closely with sports bodies to identify the stories, events and personalities that should form part of our TV, radio and online services. In the six months after the appointment in January 2013, for example, over 750 articles on women’s sport (across approximately 30 different sports) were published on the BBC Sport website. There are dedicated sections on the BBC Sport website for both women’s football and women’s cricket.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The department also recently launched a trainee scheme to provide employment opportunities for female sports journalists.  </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">A pan-BBC campaign to encourage participation</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC recently launched a new participation-focused broadcast campaign, ‘Get Inspired’, working alongside sports bodies responsible for promoting grassroots initiatives. In June 2013, we invited over 150 representatives of sports bodies from </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">across the UK to our base in Salford to discuss how best we can work with them in order to maximise the impact of the new campaign.  </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Our aim is to inspire people to try new sports and activities, through films, features, guides, and links to events and clubs near them. We are targeting the tens of millions of people in the UK that haven’t played sport in the last month. We trialled something similar during the Olympics and it proved very successful. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">At the heart of Get Inspired is our new monthly TV show, </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Inspire: the Olympic Journey</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, presented by Gabby Logan. The programmes showcase the most inspiring stories in sport, with a focus on elite sports stars. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">              </span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There will also be regular Get Inspired features across the BBC’s sports output and beyond – Blue Peter, for example, has launched a new sports badge to help increase sport participation across the country. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We have built a ‘Get Inspired’ website (</span><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/get-inspired"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/get-inspired</span></a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">) which includes a regularly updated database of more than 60 sports, a postcode finder to locate clubs and events plus links to national governing bodies. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We will monitor closely the impact of this new initiative but are confident it will harness the significant reach of the BBC to drive greater interest in sport amongst all parts of the population. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusions</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We believe that our strategy of delivering broadcast moments that bring the nation together alongside the significant breadth and depth of our cross-platform coverage is contributing to the development of women’s sports and building the profiles of female sporting role models. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The BBC has always been a strong supporter of women’s sport and we have bolstered that commitment in the last twelve months through enhanced coverage across our TV, radio and online services. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">We recognise the importance of striving to deliver a diverse mix of on-air and off-air production talent in order to better connect with audiences. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">By leveraging the reach of the BBC’s services, we expect our new pan-BBC participation scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">, ‘Get Inspired’, to drive greater audience interest in taking up sport.  </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="36" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">In summary, we believe the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> BBC is making a significant contribution to the promotion of women’s sport, providing a level of exposure, impact and representation that </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">is without equal in the UK broadcast industry. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="color:#ff0000; font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:9pt">http://www.bbc.co.uk/bbctrust/our_work/services/television/service_reviews/listed_events.html</span></p></body></html>